%% TrustyAI Explainability - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Dashboard
    participant AuthProxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>(Auth Sidecar)
    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI Service<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant ModelMesh as ModelMesh Serving
    participant KServe as KServe InferenceLogger
    participant ModelServer as KServe/ModelMesh<br/>Model Server<br/>gRPC/HTTP2
    participant Storage as Storage Backend<br/>(PVC / MinIO / DB)
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    Note over User, Prometheus: Flow 1: ModelMesh Inference Payload Processing
    ModelMesh->>TrustyAI: POST /consumer/kserve/v2<br/>8080/TCP HTTP, No Auth
    TrustyAI->>Storage: Store observation data<br/>PVC (File I/O) | MinIO (9000/TCP, TLS) | DB (3306/TCP)
    Storage-->>TrustyAI: Acknowledgment

    Note over User, Prometheus: Flow 2: KServe CloudEvent Inference Logging
    KServe->>TrustyAI: CloudEvent (HTTP)<br/>org.kubeflow.serving.inference.request<br/>org.kubeflow.serving.inference.response<br/>8080/TCP
    TrustyAI->>Storage: Store observation data<br/>PVC | MinIO | Database
    Storage-->>TrustyAI: Acknowledgment

    Note over User, Prometheus: Flow 3: Fairness/Drift Metric Computation
    User->>AuthProxy: POST /metrics/group/fairness/spd<br/>HTTPS via Route
    AuthProxy->>TrustyAI: Forward request<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    TrustyAI->>Storage: Read observation data
    Storage-->>TrustyAI: Historical data
    TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: Compute SPD/DIR metric
    TrustyAI-->>AuthProxy: Metric result (JSON)
    AuthProxy-->>User: Response

    Note over User, Prometheus: Prometheus Metrics Scraping
    Prometheus->>TrustyAI: GET /q/metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (SA)
    TrustyAI-->>Prometheus: trustyai_spd, trustyai_dir<br/>Micrometer/Prometheus format

    Note over User, Prometheus: Flow 4: Explainability (Disabled in RHOAI)
    User--xTrustyAI: POST /explainers/local/shap<br/>(DISABLED in RHOAI)
    Note right of TrustyAI: If enabled (ODH only):
    TrustyAI->>ModelServer: gRPC InferenceRequest<br/>KServe v2 Protocol<br/>plaintext or TLS
    ModelServer-->>TrustyAI: Inference Response
    TrustyAI-->>User: Explanation Result
